<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id80d9c813-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c" identifier="/us/usc/t40/s11703"><num value="11703">§ 11703.</num><heading> Procurement procedures</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">To the maximum extent practicable, the Federal Acquisition Regulatory Council shall ensure that the process for acquisition of information technology is a simplified, clear, and understandable process that specifically addresses the management of risk, incremental acquisitions, and the need to incorporate commercial information technology in a timely manner.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id80d9c814-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/217">Pub. L. 107–217</ref>, <date date="2002-08-21">Aug. 21, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1252">116 Stat. 1252</ref>, § 11704; renumbered § 11703, <ref href="/us/pl/107/314/dA/tVIII/s825/c/2">Pub. L. 107–314, div. A, title VIII, § 825(c)(2)</ref>, <date date="2002-12-02">Dec. 2, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/2616">116 Stat. 2616</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
